The paper also mentions YCSB, which is a benchmarking tool for cloud databases, indicating that the paper may also belong to cs.DB (Databases). Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of four existing protocols, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions the use of Java, which suggests that it may belong to cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper discusses the trade-off between consistency and availability, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.OS (Operating Systems).
